{"TopicId":188311,"ForumId":20,"TopicTitle":"Is there a way to resize .DDS planet texture files and make them actually work?","CreatedByName":"nubcaker","CreatedById":63205,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T14:28:27Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"nubcaker","CreatedById":63205,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T14:28:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure if this is the right place to post, but I\u0027d like to downscale the planet textures from the mod JNSQ from 8k down to 2k, for obvious performance reasons.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI assumed this would be as simple as resizing the .dds files in GIMP (using a DDS editor plugin), but when I use the resized .dds files in place of the original 8k .dds files, every planet texture in-game is broken. Completely black.\u003Cbr\u003E\nAm I overlooking something? Kinda at my wits end here.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThank in advance.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"zer0Kerbal","CreatedById":190933,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T17:40:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/63205-nubcaker/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002263205\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/63205-nubcaker/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@nubcaker\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cs\u003E need to do a double flip?\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003Erotate 180\u0022 then mirror vertically?\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nmy bad - didn\u0027t realize they were already .dds\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-17T17:58:51Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2019 05:58  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by zer0Kerbal\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GrandProtectorDark","CreatedById":183946,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T17:43:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you export them correctly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nubcaker","CreatedById":63205,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T17:55:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673554\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568742217\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022183946\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022GrandProtectorDark\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, GrandProtectorDark said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDid you export them correctly\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably not. Which compressions do I have to use? With BC3 / DXT5 I seem to be getting actual textures but the lighting is very wacky still.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-17T17:57:00Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2019 05:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by nubcaker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GrandProtectorDark","CreatedById":183946,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T18:40:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, DXT 5 is correct for some of them.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022Dry\u0022 Colormaps (those without any transparent portions, aka those for planets that don\u0027t have oceans) use DXT1\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u0022Wet\u0022 Colormaps use DXT5\u003Cbr\u003E\nNormal maps also need DXT5 (some places recommend DXT5nm but don\u0027t use it. there\u0027s some issues between that and how KSP applies planet textures)\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nHeightmaps don\u0027t need compression, but the [Format] box should have\u00A0\u0022L8\u0022 selected\u003Cbr\u003E\nBiome map don\u0027t need special compression or format.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T19:59:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDXT5nm is absolutely necessary...\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nubcaker","CreatedById":63205,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T20:41:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk I think I\u0027m getting closer and I\u0027m learning a bit along the way. The textures and lighting look right after I used DXT5nm for the normal maps but now...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XnsvxDB.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XnsvxDB.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin is red... Where did I go wrong here?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Do I have to rescale the gradient .dds files as well? What compression would they export in?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-17T20:49:49Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2019 08:49  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by nubcaker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galileo","CreatedById":150430,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T21:28:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673637\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568752876\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002263205\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022nubcaker\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n45 minutes ago, nubcaker said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOk I think I\u0027m getting closer and I\u0027m learning a bit along the way. The textures and lighting look right after I used DXT5nm for the normal maps but now...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XnsvxDB.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022XnsvxDB.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/XnsvxDB.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin is red... Where did I go wrong here?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Do I have to rescale the gradient .dds files as well? What compression would they export in?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy chance, did you accidentally set the normal map as the scaled space texture?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"nubcaker","CreatedById":63205,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-17T21:43:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223673664\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188311\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568755686\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150430\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Galileo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n35 minutes ago, Galileo said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBy chance, did you accidentally set the normal map as the scaled space texture?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow would I have done that? Not sure what you mean, sorry. I rescaled the normal map and exported in DXT5nm to the same location.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nedit: Wait I think I understand what you\u0027re saying, brb\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit 2: I got it! Everything looks nominal. I accidentally exported Kerbin00.dds with DXT5nm compression, when it should\u0027ve just been DXT5. I\u0027m guessing this is what you meant?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway looks like I\u0027m set now. Thanks fellas.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-09-17T22:05:38Z\u0022 title=\u002209/17/2019 10:05  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 17, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by nubcaker\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}